<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-04T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-04T04:00:00-05:00" n="326" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d326">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9893: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Commander in Chief of the United States Asiatic
                                Fleet</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Yarnell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-04T17:00:00+08:00">September 4, 1937—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received September 4—7:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>0004. It is recommended that every effort be made to get the Japanese and
                            Chinese Governments to withdraw their forces as recommended in the
                            American Consul General’s Shanghai despatch 648 of 4 September.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>